0 PREFIX~
The prefix command is designed to make life easier.  Instead of having to
type the same string (ie "Tell Someone ") over and over, you can use the
command 'prefix' to automatically add the prefix to each command you type.

Syntax:
    prefix                  (with no argument, turns prefix off)
    prefix tell someone     (sets the prefix to 'tell someone')

If the prefix is set, you can type...
